N. L. Hutchins, Jr., et al., plaintiffs in error, vs. S. H. Baker et al., defendants. Practice in the Supreme Court. From Milton. This cause was dismissed because there was no certificate -that the bill of exceptions sent up with the certified record -was the true original bill of exceptions. G. 1ST. Lester ; T. M. Peeples, for plaintiffs in error. .H. P. Bell ; Simmons & Howell, for defendants.

(By two judges.) If the bill of exceptions be not certified to be the true original, the cause will be dismissed. (R.) 16th January, 1872.
